description:
secretx-aws-sm/src/lib.rs:91-120 (map_get_error) and 122-150 (map_put_error) are nearly identical. The only differences:

- Generic parameter: SdkError<GetSecretValueError> vs SdkError<PutSecretValueError>
- A one-line comment about the set of permanent error variants

Both have the same shape:
  1. as_service_error() → if Some, check is_resource_not_found_exception() → NotFound
  2. Check meta().code() for ThrottlingException/RequestThrottledException, or is_internal_service_error() → Unavailable
  3. Otherwise → Backend
  4. If as_service_error() returned None (transport/network) → Unavailable

This is the same finding as crate-secretsx-mf3q for secretx-aws-kms.

Suggested refactor — a single generic helper parameterised by predicates:

    use aws_smithy_runtime_api::client::result::SdkError;
    use aws_smithy_types::error::metadata::ProvideErrorMetadata;
    use std::error::Error;

    fn map_aws_error<E, R>(
        e: SdkError<E, R>,
        is_not_found: impl FnOnce(&E) -> bool,
        is_internal: impl FnOnce(&E) -> bool,
    ) -> SecretError
    where
        E: ProvideErrorMetadata + std::fmt::Display + Error + Send + Sync + 'static,
        SdkError<E, R>: Error + Send + Sync + 'static,
    {
        if let Some(svc) = e.as_service_error() {
            if is_not_found(svc) {
                return SecretError::NotFound;
            }
            let code = svc.meta().code().unwrap_or("");
            let transient = code == "ThrottlingException"
                || code == "RequestThrottledException"
                || is_internal(svc);
            return if transient {
                SecretError::Unavailable { backend: BACKEND, source: svc.to_string().into() }
            } else {
                SecretError::Backend { backend: BACKEND, source: svc.to_string().into() }
            };
        }
        SecretError::Unavailable { backend: BACKEND, source: e.into() }
    }

Call sites:

    .map_err(|e| map_aws_error(e, |s| s.is_resource_not_found_exception(), |s| s.is_internal_service_error()))?

Note: bound "SdkError: Error + Send + Sync" may need to be tightened to match what ".into()" requires for Box<dyn Error + Send + Sync>. Verify against the actual aws-smithy-runtime-api version. This refactor pays for itself once a third backend in the same shape (e.g. when adding aws-secrets-manager batch-get) needs the same logic.

If the refactor is judged not worth it: at minimum the comment at line 97-99 should be updated to match the comment at line 128-129 (one mentions specific permanent variants, the other doesn't); they should say the same thing or the difference should be intentional.
